This paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). It also considers information-theoretic limitations, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper's focus on artificial agents and their behavior suggests that it could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper's exploration of the behavior of agents in an infinite time horizon suggests that it could also be categorized under control systems (cs.SY).
